# ── Row 1: EPOLLERR ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
row1: {
  grid-columns: 3
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "EPOLLERR" {
    style: {
      fill: "#FDECEA"
      font-color: "#B71C1C"
      bold: true
      font-size: 15
      stroke: "#E57373"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font: mono
    }
  }
  c2: |'md
Asynchronous socket error  
— RST segment received from peer  
— Non-blocking `connect()` failed  
— I/O error at network layer  
— Out-of-band data condition
'| {
    style: {
      fill: "#FFF8F8"
      stroke: "#E57373"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font-size: 13
    }
  }
  c3: |'md
→ **`REACTOR_ERROR`**  
1. `getsockopt(fd, SOL_SOCKET, SO_ERROR, &err, &len)`  
   to retrieve the specific `errno`  
2. Log the error code  
3. **Close the connection immediately**  
Do NOT attempt further reads/writes
'| {
    style: {
      fill: "#FFF8F8"
      stroke: "#E57373"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font-size: 13
    }
  }
}

# ── Row 2: EPOLLHUP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
row2: {
  grid-columns: 3
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "EPOLLHUP" {
    style: {
      fill: "#FFF3E0"
      font-color: "#E65100"
      bold: true
      font-size: 15
      stroke: "#FFB74D"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font: mono
    }
  }
  c2: |'md
Peer closed its write side  
— TCP FIN received (remote half-close)  
— Receive buffer may still have data  
— No new data will arrive after drain  
— Common on normal connection close
'| {
    style: {
      fill: "#FFFBF5"
      stroke: "#FFB74D"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font-size: 13
    }
  }
  c3: |'md
→ **`REACTOR_ERROR`**  
1. Read any remaining data still in  
   the kernel receive buffer  
2. `read()` will return `n > 0` then `0` (EOF)  
3. On `n == 0`: **close the connection**  
Connection is half-closed; writes may still work
'| {
    style: {
      fill: "#FFFBF5"
      stroke: "#FFB74D"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font-size: 13
    }
  }
}

# ── Row 3: EPOLLRDHUP ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
row3: {
  grid-columns: 3
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "EPOLLRDHUP" {
    style: {
      fill: "#E8F5E9"
      font-color: "#2E7D32"
      bold: true
      font-size: 15
      stroke: "#81C784"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font: mono
    }
  }
  c2: |'md
Specific remote half-close signal  
— Linux kernel ≥ 2.6.17 only  
— More precise than EPOLLHUP  
— Peer sent TCP FIN (write-side closed)  
— Must explicitly subscribe: add  
  `EPOLLRDHUP` to `epoll_ctl` flags
'| {
    style: {
      fill: "#F5FFF6"
      stroke: "#81C784"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font-size: 13
    }
  }
  c3: |'md
→ **`REACTOR_ERROR`** (map same as EPOLLHUP)  
1. Stop reading: no new data will arrive  
2. Optionally flush any pending write buffer  
3. Begin graceful close sequence  
Faster detection than waiting for `read()` → 0
'| {
    style: {
      fill: "#F5FFF6"
      stroke: "#81C784"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font-size: 13
    }
  }
}

# ── Row 4: EPOLLIN|EPOLLERR simultaneous ─────────────────────────────────────
row4: {
  grid-columns: 3
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "EPOLLIN\n|\nEPOLLERR" {
    style: {
      fill: "#EDE7F6"
      font-color: "#4527A0"
      bold: true
      font-size: 14
      stroke: "#9575CD"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font: mono
    }
  }
  c2: |'md
Both flags delivered simultaneously  
— Data available in receive buffer AND  
— Asynchronous error has also occurred  
— Common during RST with queued data  
— Also occurs on EPOLLHUP + data present  
— Can arrive in a single `epoll_wait` event
'| {
    style: {
      fill: "#F9F7FF"
      stroke: "#9575CD"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font-size: 13
    }
  }
  c3: |'md
→ **`REACTOR_READ | REACTOR_ERROR`**  
**Handle ERROR first — always:**  
c
if (events & REACTOR_ERROR) {
    conn_close(conn);   // ← first
    return;             // ← never reach READ
}
if (events & REACTOR_READ) { ... }

Data after an error is unreliable; discard it
'| {
    style: {
      fill: "#F9F7FF"
      stroke: "#9575CD"
      stroke-width: 1
      border-radius: 0
      font-size: 13
    }
  }
}

# ── Canonical callback skeleton ───────────────────────────────────────────────
skeleton: |'go
// Canonical reactor I/O callback — correct error-check ordering
void http_io_callback(int fd, uint32_t events, void *udata) {
    conn_t *conn = udata;
    // ① ERROR check FIRST — cannot be deferred
    if (events & REACTOR_ERROR) {
        int err = 0; socklen_t len = sizeof(err);
        getsockopt(fd, SOL_SOCKET, SO_ERROR, &err, &len);
        conn_close(conn);   // timer cancel → deregister → close(fd) → free
        return;             // NEVER fall through to READ/WRITE after error
    }
    // ② READ — safe only if no error
    if (events & REACTOR_READ)  conn_handle_read(conn);
    if (conn->state == CLOSING) return;   // read may have closed it
    // ③ WRITE — safe only if connection still alive
    if (events & REACTOR_WRITE) conn_handle_write(conn);
}
'| {
  near: bottom-center
  style: {
    fill: "#1E1E2E"
    font-color: "#CDD6F4"
    stroke: "#585B70"
    stroke-width: 2
    border-radius: 6
    font-size: 12
  }
}